    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A Chinese temple style influenced by earlier Japanese structural traditions but with a tendency toward minutely detailed, intricate surface decoration. A famous example is Engaku-ji in Kamakura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000025171/Lee, History of Far Eastern Art (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un estilo chino de templo influenciado por tradiciones estructurales japonesas anteriores pero con una tendencia hacia la decoración superficial minuciosa y detallada. Un ejemplo famoso es Engaku-ji en Kamakura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chinese tempelstijl die is beïnvloed door oudere Japanse bouwtradities, maar met opvallend fijn gedetailleerde, complexe oppervlaktedecoraties. Een beroemd voorbeeld is Engaku-ji in Kamakura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>受到早期日本建築傳統影響的中國廟宇風格。相較於日本建築，唐樣具有較多細緻繁複的表面裝飾。最有名的代表為日本鎌倉之「圓覺寺」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
